73QStyleOptionMenuItem QComboMenuDelegate::getStyleOption(const QStyleOptionViewItem &option,
74 const QModelIndex &index) const
75{
76 QStyleOptionMenuItem menuOption;
77
78 QPalette resolvedpalette = option.palette.resolve(other: QApplication::palette(className: "QMenu"));
79 QVariant value = index.data(arole: Qt::ForegroundRole);
80 if (value.canConvert<QBrush>()) {
81 resolvedpalette.setBrush(acr: QPalette::WindowText, abrush: qvariant_cast<QBrush>(v: value));
82 resolvedpalette.setBrush(acr: QPalette::ButtonText, abrush: qvariant_cast<QBrush>(v: value));
83 resolvedpalette.setBrush(acr: QPalette::Text, abrush: qvariant_cast<QBrush>(v: value));
84 }
85 menuOption.palette = resolvedpalette;
86 menuOption.state = QStyle::State_None;
87 if (mCombo->window()->isActiveWindow())
88 menuOption.state = QStyle::State_Active;
89 if ((option.state & QStyle::State_Enabled) && (index.model()->flags(index) & Qt::ItemIsEnabled))
90 menuOption.state |= QStyle::State_Enabled;
91 else
92 menuOption.palette.setCurrentColorGroup(QPalette::Disabled);
93 if (option.state & QStyle::State_Selected)
94 menuOption.state |= QStyle::State_Selected;
95 menuOption.checkType = QStyleOptionMenuItem::NonExclusive;
96 // a valid checkstate means that the model has checkable items
97 const QVariant checkState = index.data(arole: Qt::CheckStateRole);
98 if (!checkState.isValid()) {
99 menuOption.checked = mCombo->currentIndex() == index.row();
100 } else {
101 menuOption.checked = qvariant_cast<int>(v: checkState) == Qt::Checked;
102 menuOption.state |= qvariant_cast<int>(v: checkState) == Qt::Checked
103 ? QStyle::State_On : QStyle::State_Off;
104 }
105 if (QComboBoxDelegate::isSeparator(index))
106 menuOption.menuItemType = QStyleOptionMenuItem::Separator;
107 else
108 menuOption.menuItemType = QStyleOptionMenuItem::Normal;
109
110 QVariant variant = index.model()->data(index, role: Qt::DecorationRole);
111 switch (variant.userType()) {
112 case QMetaType::QIcon:
113 menuOption.icon = qvariant_cast<QIcon>(v: variant);
114 break;
115 case QMetaType::QColor: {
116 static QPixmap pixmap(option.decorationSize);
117 pixmap.fill(fillColor: qvariant_cast<QColor>(v: variant));
118 menuOption.icon = pixmap;
119 break; }
120 default:
121 menuOption.icon = qvariant_cast<QPixmap>(v: variant);
122 break;
123 }
124 if (index.data(arole: Qt::BackgroundRole).canConvert<QBrush>()) {
125 menuOption.palette.setBrush(cg: QPalette::All, cr: QPalette::Window,
126 brush: qvariant_cast<QBrush>(v: index.data(arole: Qt::BackgroundRole)));
127 }
128 menuOption.text = index.model()->data(index, role: Qt::DisplayRole).toString().replace(c: u'&', after: "&&"_L1);
129 menuOption.reservedShortcutWidth = 0;
130 menuOption.maxIconWidth = option.decorationSize.width() + 4;
131 menuOption.menuRect = option.rect;
132 menuOption.rect = option.rect;
133
134 // Make sure fonts set on the model or on the combo box, in
135 // that order, also override the font for the popup menu.
136 QVariant fontRoleData = index.data(arole: Qt::FontRole);
137 if (fontRoleData.isValid()) {
138 menuOption.font = qvariant_cast<QFont>(v: fontRoleData);
139 } else if (mCombo->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_SetFont)
140 || mCombo->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_MacSmallSize)
141 || mCombo->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_MacMiniSize)
142 || mCombo->font() != qt_app_fonts_hash()->value(key: "QComboBox", defaultValue: QFont())) {
143 menuOption.font = mCombo->font();
144 } else {
145 menuOption.font = qt_app_fonts_hash()->value(key: "QComboMenuItem", defaultValue: mCombo->font());
146 }
147
148 menuOption.fontMetrics = QFontMetrics(menuOption.font);
149
150 return menuOption;
151}

153bool QComboMenuDelegate::editorEvent(QEvent *event, QAbstractItemModel *model,
154 const QStyleOptionViewItem &option, const QModelIndex &index)
155{
156 Q_ASSERT(event);
157 Q_ASSERT(model);
158
159 // make sure that the item is checkable
160 Qt::ItemFlags flags = model->flags(index);
161 if (!(flags & Qt::ItemIsUserCheckable) || !(option.state & QStyle::State_Enabled)
162 || !(flags & Qt::ItemIsEnabled))
163 return false;
164
165 // make sure that we have a check state
166 const QVariant checkState = index.data(arole: Qt::CheckStateRole);
167 if (!checkState.isValid())
168 return false;
169
170 // make sure that we have the right event type
171 if ((event->type() == QEvent::MouseButtonRelease)
172 || (event->type() == QEvent::MouseButtonDblClick)
173 || (event->type() == QEvent::MouseButtonPress)) {
174 QMouseEvent *me = static_cast<QMouseEvent*>(event);
175 if (me->button() != Qt::LeftButton)
176 return false;
177
178 if ((event->type() == QEvent::MouseButtonPress)
179 || (event->type() == QEvent::MouseButtonDblClick)) {
180 pressedIndex = index.row();
181 return false;
182 }
183
184 if (index.row() != pressedIndex)
185 return false;
186 pressedIndex = -1;
187
188 } else if (event->type() == QEvent::KeyPress) {
189 if (static_cast<QKeyEvent*>(event)->key() != Qt::Key_Space
190 && static_cast<QKeyEvent*>(event)->key() != Qt::Key_Select)
191 return false;
192 } else {
193 return false;
194 }
195
196 // we don't support user-tristate items in QComboBox (not implemented in any style)
197 Qt::CheckState newState = (static_cast<Qt::CheckState>(checkState.toInt()) == Qt::Checked)
198 ? Qt::Unchecked : Qt::Checked;
199 return model->setData(index, value: newState, role: Qt::CheckStateRole);
200}

202#if QT_CONFIG(completer)
203void QComboBoxPrivate::_q_completerActivated(const QModelIndex &index)
204{
205 Q_Q(QComboBox);
206#if QT_CONFIG(proxymodel)
207 if (index.isValid() && q->completer()) {
208 QAbstractProxyModel *proxy = qobject_cast<QAbstractProxyModel *>(object: q->completer()->completionModel());
209 if (proxy) {
210 const QModelIndex &completerIndex = proxy->mapToSource(proxyIndex: index);
211 int row = -1;
212 if (completerIndex.model() == model) {
213 row = completerIndex.row();
214 } else {
215 // if QCompleter uses a proxy model to host widget's one - map again
216 QAbstractProxyModel *completerProxy = qobject_cast<QAbstractProxyModel *>(object: q->completer()->model());
217 if (completerProxy && completerProxy->sourceModel() == model) {
218 row = completerProxy->mapToSource(proxyIndex: completerIndex).row();
219 } else {
220 QString match = q->completer()->model()->data(index: completerIndex).toString();
221 row = q->findText(text: match, flags: matchFlags());
222 }
223 }
224 q->setCurrentIndex(row);
225 emitActivated(index: currentIndex);
226 }
227 }
228#endif
229}
230#endif // QT_CONFIG(completer)

240 q->update(q->rect());

244{
245 Q_Q(QComboBox);
246 if (lineEdit) {
247 lineEdit->setText(QString());
248 updateLineEditGeometry();
249 }
250 trySetValidIndex();
251 modelChanged();
252 q->update();
253}

259
260void QComboBoxPrivate::trySetValidIndex()
261{
262 Q_Q(QComboBox);
263 bool currentReset = false;
264
265 const int rowCount = q->count();
266 for (int pos = 0; pos < rowCount; ++pos) {
267 const QModelIndex idx(model->index(row: pos, column: modelColumn, parent: root));
268 if (idx.flags() & Qt::ItemIsEnabled) {
269 setCurrentIndex(idx);
270 currentReset = true;
271 break;
272 }
273 }
274
275 if (!currentReset)
276 setCurrentIndex(QModelIndex());
277}

287bool QComboBoxPrivate::updateHoverControl(const QPoint &pos)
288{
289
290 Q_Q(QComboBox);
291 QRect lastHoverRect = hoverRect;
292 QStyle::SubControl lastHoverControl = hoverControl;
293 bool doesHover = q->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_Hover);
294 if (lastHoverControl != newHoverControl(pos) && doesHover) {
295 q->update(lastHoverRect);
296 q->update(hoverRect);
297 return true;
298 }
299 return !doesHover;
300}
301
302QStyle::SubControl QComboBoxPrivate::newHoverControl(const QPoint &pos)
303{
304 Q_Q(QComboBox);
305 QStyleOptionComboBox opt;
306 q->initStyleOption(option: &opt);
307 opt.subControls = QStyle::SC_All;
308 hoverControl = q->style()->hitTestComplexControl(cc: QStyle::CC_ComboBox, opt: &opt, pt: pos, widget: q);
309 hoverRect = (hoverControl != QStyle::SC_None)
310 ? q->style()->subControlRect(cc: QStyle::CC_ComboBox, opt: &opt, sc: hoverControl, widget: q)
311 : QRect();
312 return hoverControl;
313}

315/*
316 Computes a size hint based on the maximum width
317 for the items in the combobox.
318*/
319int QComboBoxPrivate::computeWidthHint() const
320{
321 Q_Q(const QComboBox);
322
323 int width = 0;
324 const int count = q->count();
325 const int iconWidth = q->iconSize().width() + 4;
326 const QFontMetrics &fontMetrics = q->fontMetrics();
327
328 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
329 const int textWidth = fontMetrics.horizontalAdvance(q->itemText(index: i));
330 if (q->itemIcon(index: i).isNull())
331 width = (qMax(a: width, b: textWidth));
332 else
333 width = (qMax(a: width, b: textWidth + iconWidth));
334 }
335
336 QStyleOptionComboBox opt;
337 q->initStyleOption(option: &opt);
338 QSize tmp(width, 0);
339 tmp = q->style()->sizeFromContents(ct: QStyle::CT_ComboBox, opt: &opt, contentsSize: tmp, w: q);
340 return tmp.width();
341}
342
343QSize QComboBoxPrivate::recomputeSizeHint(QSize &sh) const
344{
345 Q_Q(const QComboBox);
346 if (!sh.isValid()) {
347 bool hasIcon = sizeAdjustPolicy == QComboBox::AdjustToMinimumContentsLengthWithIcon;
348 int count = q->count();
349 QSize iconSize = q->iconSize();
350 const QFontMetrics &fm = q->fontMetrics();
351
352 // text width
353 if (&sh == &sizeHint || minimumContentsLength == 0) {
354 switch (sizeAdjustPolicy) {
355 case QComboBox::AdjustToContents:
356 case QComboBox::AdjustToContentsOnFirstShow:
357 if (count == 0) {
358 sh.rwidth() = 7 * fm.horizontalAdvance(u'x');
359 } else {
360 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
361 if (!q->itemIcon(index: i).isNull()) {
362 hasIcon = true;
363 sh.setWidth(qMax(a: sh.width(), b: fm.boundingRect(text: q->itemText(index: i)).width() + iconSize.width() + 4));
364 } else {
365 sh.setWidth(qMax(a: sh.width(), b: fm.boundingRect(text: q->itemText(index: i)).width()));
366 }
367 }
368 }
369 break;
370 case QComboBox::AdjustToMinimumContentsLengthWithIcon:
371 ;
372 }
373 } else {
374 for (int i = 0; i < count && !hasIcon; ++i)
375 hasIcon = !q->itemIcon(index: i).isNull();
376 }
377 if (minimumContentsLength > 0)
378 sh.setWidth(qMax(a: sh.width(), b: minimumContentsLength * fm.horizontalAdvance(u'X') + (hasIcon ? iconSize.width() + 4 : 0)));
379 if (!placeholderText.isEmpty())
380 sh.setWidth(qMax(a: sh.width(), b: fm.boundingRect(text: placeholderText).width()));
381
382
383 // height
384 sh.setHeight(qMax(a: qCeil(v: QFontMetricsF(fm).height()), b: 14) + 2);
385 if (hasIcon) {
386 sh.setHeight(qMax(a: sh.height(), b: iconSize.height() + 2));
387 }
388
389 // add style and strut values
390 QStyleOptionComboBox opt;
391 q->initStyleOption(option: &opt);
392 sh = q->style()->sizeFromContents(ct: QStyle::CT_ComboBox, opt: &opt, contentsSize: sh, w: q);
393 }
394 return sh;
395}

416void QComboBoxPrivateContainer::timerEvent(QTimerEvent *timerEvent)
417{
418 if (timerEvent->timerId() == adjustSizeTimer.timerId()) {
419 adjustSizeTimer.stop();
420 if (combo->sizeAdjustPolicy() == QComboBox::AdjustToContents) {
421 combo->updateGeometry();

423 combo->update();
424 }
425 }

428void QComboBoxPrivateContainer::resizeEvent(QResizeEvent *e)
429{
430 QStyleOptionComboBox opt = comboStyleOption();
431 if (combo->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: combo)) {
432 QStyleOption myOpt;
433 myOpt.initFrom(w: this);
434 QStyleHintReturnMask mask;
435 if (combo->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_Menu_Mask, opt: &myOpt, widget: this, returnData: &mask)) {
436 setMask(mask.region);
437 }
438 } else {
439 clearMask();
440 }
441 QFrame::resizeEvent(event: e);
442}

444void QComboBoxPrivateContainer::paintEvent(QPaintEvent *e)
445{
446 QStyleOptionComboBox cbOpt = comboStyleOption();
447 if (combo->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &cbOpt, widget: combo)
448 && mask().isEmpty()) {
449 QStyleOption opt;
450 opt.initFrom(w: this);
451 QPainter p(this);
452 style()->drawPrimitive(pe: QStyle::PE_PanelMenu, opt: &opt, p: &p, w: this);
453 }
454
455 QFrame::paintEvent(e);
456}

458QComboBoxPrivateContainer::QComboBoxPrivateContainer(QAbstractItemView *itemView, QComboBox *parent)
459 : QFrame(parent, Qt::Popup), combo(parent)
460{
461 // we need the combobox and itemview
462 Q_ASSERT(parent);
463 Q_ASSERT(itemView);
464
465 setAttribute(Qt::WA_WindowPropagation);
466 setAttribute(Qt::WA_X11NetWmWindowTypeCombo);
467
468 // setup container
469 blockMouseReleaseTimer.setSingleShot(true);
470
471 // we need a vertical layout
472 QBoxLayout *layout = new QBoxLayout(QBoxLayout::TopToBottom, this);
473 layout->setSpacing(0);
474 layout->setContentsMargins(QMargins());
475
476 // set item view
477 setItemView(itemView);
478
479 // add scroller arrows if style needs them
480 QStyleOptionComboBox opt = comboStyleOption();
481 const bool usePopup = combo->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: combo);
482 if (usePopup) {
483 top = new QComboBoxPrivateScroller(QAbstractSlider::SliderSingleStepSub, this);
484 bottom = new QComboBoxPrivateScroller(QAbstractSlider::SliderSingleStepAdd, this);
485 top->hide();
486 bottom->hide();
487 } else {
488 setLineWidth(1);
489 }
490
491 if (top) {
492 layout->insertWidget(index: 0, widget: top);
493 connect(sender: top, SIGNAL(doScroll(int)), receiver: this, SLOT(scrollItemView(int)));
494 }
495 if (bottom) {
496 layout->addWidget(bottom);
497 connect(sender: bottom, SIGNAL(doScroll(int)), receiver: this, SLOT(scrollItemView(int)));
498 }
499
500 // Some styles (Mac) have a margin at the top and bottom of the popup.
501 layout->insertSpacing(index: 0, size: 0);
502 layout->addSpacing(size: 0);
503 updateStyleSettings();
504}

522/*
523 Hides or shows the scrollers when we emulate a popupmenu
524*/
525void QComboBoxPrivateContainer::updateScrollers()
526{
527#if QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
528 if (!top || !bottom)
529 return;
530
531 if (isVisible() == false)
532 return;
533
534 QStyleOptionComboBox opt = comboStyleOption();
535 if (combo->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: combo) &&
536 view->verticalScrollBar()->minimum() < view->verticalScrollBar()->maximum()) {
537
538 bool needTop = view->verticalScrollBar()->value()
539 > (view->verticalScrollBar()->minimum() + topMargin());
540 bool needBottom = view->verticalScrollBar()->value()
541 < (view->verticalScrollBar()->maximum() - bottomMargin() - topMargin());
542 if (needTop)
543 top->show();
544 else
545 top->hide();
546 if (needBottom)
547 bottom->show();
548 else
549 bottom->hide();
550 } else {
551 top->hide();
552 bottom->hide();
553 }
554#endif // QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
555}

574/*!
575 Sets the item view to be used for the combobox popup.
576*/
577void QComboBoxPrivateContainer::setItemView(QAbstractItemView *itemView)
578{
579 Q_ASSERT(itemView);
580
581 // clean up old one
582 if (view) {
583 view->removeEventFilter(obj: this);
584 view->viewport()->removeEventFilter(obj: this);
585#if QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
586 disconnect(sender: view->verticalScrollBar(), SIGNAL(valueChanged(int)),
587 receiver: this, SLOT(updateScrollers()));
588 disconnect(sender: view->verticalScrollBar(), SIGNAL(rangeChanged(int,int)),
589 receiver: this, SLOT(updateScrollers()));
590#endif
591 disconnect(sender: view, SIGNAL(destroyed()),
592 receiver: this, SLOT(viewDestroyed()));
593
594 if (isAncestorOf(child: view))
595 delete view;
596 view = nullptr;
597 }
598
599 // setup the item view
600 view = itemView;
601 view->setParent(this);
602 view->setAttribute(Qt::WA_MacShowFocusRect, on: false);
603 qobject_cast<QBoxLayout*>(object: layout())->insertWidget(index: top ? 2 : 0, widget: view);
604 view->setSizePolicy(hor: QSizePolicy::Ignored, ver: QSizePolicy::Ignored);
605 view->installEventFilter(filterObj: this);
606 view->viewport()->installEventFilter(filterObj: this);
607 view->setHorizontalScrollBarPolicy(Qt::ScrollBarAlwaysOff);
608 QStyleOptionComboBox opt = comboStyleOption();
609 const bool usePopup = combo->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: combo);
610#if QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
611 if (usePopup)
612 view->setVerticalScrollBarPolicy(Qt::ScrollBarAlwaysOff);
613#endif
614 if (combo->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_ListMouseTracking, opt: &opt, widget: combo) ||
615 usePopup) {
616 view->setMouseTracking(true);
617 }
618 view->setSelectionMode(QAbstractItemView::SingleSelection);
619 view->setFrameStyle(QFrame::NoFrame);
620 view->setLineWidth(0);
621 view->setEditTriggers(QAbstractItemView::NoEditTriggers);
622#if QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
623 connect(sender: view->verticalScrollBar(), SIGNAL(valueChanged(int)),
624 receiver: this, SLOT(updateScrollers()));
625 connect(sender: view->verticalScrollBar(), SIGNAL(rangeChanged(int,int)),
626 receiver: this, SLOT(updateScrollers()));
627#endif
628 connect(sender: view, SIGNAL(destroyed()),
629 receiver: this, SLOT(viewDestroyed()));
630}

632/*!
633 Returns the top/bottom vertical margin of the view.
634*/
635int QComboBoxPrivateContainer::topMargin() const
636{
637 if (const QListView *lview = qobject_cast<const QListView*>(object: view))
638 return lview->spacing();
639#if QT_CONFIG(tableview)
640 if (const QTableView *tview = qobject_cast<const QTableView*>(object: view))
641 return tview->showGrid() ? 1 : 0;
642#endif
643 return 0;
644}
645
646/*!
647 Returns the spacing between the items in the view.
648*/
649int QComboBoxPrivateContainer::spacing() const
650{
651 QListView *lview = qobject_cast<QListView*>(object: view);
652 if (lview)
653 return 2 * lview->spacing(); // QListView::spacing is the padding around the item.
654#if QT_CONFIG(tableview)
655 QTableView *tview = qobject_cast<QTableView*>(object: view);
656 if (tview)
657 return tview->showGrid() ? 1 : 0;
658#endif
659 return 0;
660}
661
662void QComboBoxPrivateContainer::updateTopBottomMargin()
663{
664 if (!layout() || layout()->count() < 1)
665 return;
666
667 QBoxLayout *boxLayout = qobject_cast<QBoxLayout *>(object: layout());
668 if (!boxLayout)
669 return;
670
671 const QStyleOptionComboBox opt = comboStyleOption();
672 const bool usePopup = combo->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: combo);
673 const int margin = usePopup ? combo->style()->pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_MenuVMargin, option: &opt, widget: combo) : 0;
674
675 QSpacerItem *topSpacer = boxLayout->itemAt(0)->spacerItem();
676 if (topSpacer)
677 topSpacer->changeSize(w: 0, h: margin, hData: QSizePolicy::Minimum, vData: QSizePolicy::Fixed);
678
679 QSpacerItem *bottomSpacer = boxLayout->itemAt(boxLayout->count() - 1)->spacerItem();
680 if (bottomSpacer && bottomSpacer != topSpacer)
681 bottomSpacer->changeSize(w: 0, h: margin, hData: QSizePolicy::Minimum, vData: QSizePolicy::Fixed);
682
683 boxLayout->invalidate();
684}

704
705bool QComboBoxPrivateContainer::eventFilter(QObject *o, QEvent *e)
706{
707 switch (e->type()) {
708 case QEvent::ShortcutOverride: {
709 QKeyEvent *keyEvent = static_cast<QKeyEvent*>(e);
710 switch (keyEvent->key()) {
711 case Qt::Key_Enter:
712 case Qt::Key_Return:
713#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
714 case Qt::Key_Select:
715#endif
716 if (view->currentIndex().isValid() && view->currentIndex().flags().testFlag(flag: Qt::ItemIsEnabled)) {
717 combo->hidePopup();
718 emit itemSelected(view->currentIndex());
719 }
720 return true;
721 case Qt::Key_Down:
722 if (!(keyEvent->modifiers() & Qt::AltModifier))
723 break;
724 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
725 case Qt::Key_F4:
726 combo->hidePopup();
727 return true;
728 default:
729#if QT_CONFIG(shortcut)
730 if (keyEvent->matches(key: QKeySequence::Cancel) && isVisible()) {
731 keyEvent->accept();
732 return true;
733 }
734#endif
735 break;
736 }
737 break;
738 }
739 case QEvent::MouseMove:
740 if (isVisible()) {
741 QMouseEvent *m = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
742 QWidget *widget = static_cast<QWidget *>(o);
743 QPoint vector = widget->mapToGlobal(m->position().toPoint()) - initialClickPosition;
744 if (vector.manhattanLength() > 9 && blockMouseReleaseTimer.isActive())
745 blockMouseReleaseTimer.stop();
746 QModelIndex indexUnderMouse = view->indexAt(point: m->position().toPoint());
747 if (indexUnderMouse.isValid()
748 && !QComboBoxDelegate::isSeparator(index: indexUnderMouse)) {
749 view->setCurrentIndex(indexUnderMouse);
750 }
751 }
752 break;
753 case QEvent::MouseButtonPress:
754 maybeIgnoreMouseButtonRelease = false;
755 break;
756 case QEvent::MouseButtonRelease: {
757 bool ignoreEvent = maybeIgnoreMouseButtonRelease && popupTimer.elapsed() < QApplication::doubleClickInterval();
758
759 QMouseEvent *m = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
760 if (isVisible() && view->rect().contains(p: m->position().toPoint()) && view->currentIndex().isValid()
761 && !blockMouseReleaseTimer.isActive() && !ignoreEvent
762 && (view->currentIndex().flags().testFlag(flag: Qt::ItemIsEnabled))
763 && (view->currentIndex().flags().testFlag(flag: Qt::ItemIsSelectable))) {
764 combo->hidePopup();
765 emit itemSelected(view->currentIndex());
766 return true;
767 }
768 break;
769 }
770 default:
771 break;
772 }
773 return QFrame::eventFilter(watched: o, event: e);
774}

831 \enum QComboBox::InsertPolicy
832
833 This enum specifies what the QComboBox should do when a new string is
834 entered by the user.
835
836 \value NoInsert The string will not be inserted into the combobox.
837 \value InsertAtTop The string will be inserted as the first item in the combobox.
838 \value InsertAtCurrent The current item will be \e replaced by the string.
839 \value InsertAtBottom The string will be inserted after the last item in the combobox.
840 \value InsertAfterCurrent The string is inserted after the current item in the combobox.
841 \value InsertBeforeCurrent The string is inserted before the current item in the combobox.
842 \value InsertAlphabetically The string is inserted in the alphabetic order in the combobox.
843*/

847
848 This enum specifies how the size hint of the QComboBox should
849 adjust when new content is added or content changes.
850
851 \value AdjustToContents The combobox will always adjust to the contents
852 \value AdjustToContentsOnFirstShow The combobox will adjust to its contents the first time it is shown.
853 \value AdjustToMinimumContentsLengthWithIcon The combobox will adjust to \l minimumContentsLength plus space for an icon.
854 For performance reasons use this policy on large models.
855*/

932/*!
933 \class QComboBox
934 \brief The QComboBox widget is a combined button and popup list.
935
936 \ingroup basicwidgets
937 \inmodule QtWidgets
938
939 \image windows-combobox.png
940
941 A QComboBox provides a means of presenting a list of options to the user
942 in a way that takes up the minimum amount of screen space.
943
944 A combobox is a selection widget that displays the current item,
945 and can pop up a list of selectable items. A combobox may be editable,
946 allowing the user to modify each item in the list.
947
948 Comboboxes can contain pixmaps as well as strings; the
949 insertItem() and setItemText() functions are suitably overloaded.
950 For editable comboboxes, the function clearEditText() is provided,
951 to clear the displayed string without changing the combobox's
952 contents.
953
954 There are three signals emitted if the current item of a combobox
955 changes, currentIndexChanged(), currentTextChanged() and activated().
956 currentIndexChanged() and currentTextChanged() are always emitted
957 regardless if the change
958 was done programmatically or by user interaction, while
959 activated() is only emitted when the change is caused by user
960 interaction. The highlighted() signal is emitted when the user
961 highlights an item in the combobox popup list. All three signals
962 exist in two versions, one with a QString argument and one with an
963 \c int argument. If the user selects or highlights a pixmap, only
964 the \c int signals are emitted. Whenever the text of an editable
965 combobox is changed the editTextChanged() signal is emitted.
966
967 When the user enters a new string in an editable combobox, the
968 widget may or may not insert it, and it can insert it in several
969 locations. The default policy is \l InsertAtBottom but you can change
970 this using setInsertPolicy().
971
972 It is possible to constrain the input to an editable combobox
973 using QValidator; see setValidator(). By default, any input is
974 accepted.
975
976 A combobox can be populated using the insert functions,
977 insertItem() and insertItems() for example. Items can be
978 changed with setItemText(). An item can be removed with
979 removeItem() and all items can be removed with clear(). The text
980 of the current item is returned by currentText(), and the text of
981 a numbered item is returned with text(). The current item can be
982 set with setCurrentIndex(). The number of items in the combobox is
983 returned by count(); the maximum number of items can be set with
984 setMaxCount(). You can allow editing using setEditable(). For
985 editable comboboxes you can set auto-completion using
986 setCompleter() and whether or not the user can add duplicates
987 is set with setDuplicatesEnabled().
988
989 QComboBox uses the \l{Model/View Programming}{model/view
990 framework} for its popup list and to store its items. By default
991 a QStandardItemModel stores the items and a QListView subclass
992 displays the popuplist. You can access the model and view directly
993 (with model() and view()), but QComboBox also provides functions
994 to set and get item data (e.g., setItemData() and itemText()). You
995 can also set a new model and view (with setModel() and setView()).
996 For the text and icon in the combobox label, the data in the model
997 that has the Qt::DisplayRole and Qt::DecorationRole is used. Note
998 that you cannot alter the \l{QAbstractItemView::}{SelectionMode}
999 of the view(), e.g., by using
1000 \l{QAbstractItemView::}{setSelectionMode()}.
1001
1002 \sa QLineEdit, QSpinBox, QRadioButton, QButtonGroup
1003*/
1004
1005void QComboBoxPrivate::init()
1006{
1007 Q_Q(QComboBox);
1008#ifdef Q_OS_MACOS
1009 // On OS X, only line edits and list views always get tab focus. It's only
1010 // when we enable full keyboard access that other controls can get tab focus.
1011 // When it's not editable, a combobox looks like a button, and it behaves as
1012 // such in this respect.
1013 if (!q->isEditable())
1014 q->setFocusPolicy(Qt::TabFocus);
1015 else
1016#endif
1017 q->setFocusPolicy(Qt::WheelFocus);
1018
1019 q->setSizePolicy(QSizePolicy(QSizePolicy::Preferred, QSizePolicy::Fixed,
1020 QSizePolicy::ComboBox));
1021 setLayoutItemMargins(element: QStyle::SE_ComboBoxLayoutItem);
1022 q->setModel(new QStandardItemModel(0, 1, q));
1023 if (!q->isEditable())
1024 q->setAttribute(Qt::WA_InputMethodEnabled, on: false);
1025 else
1026 q->setAttribute(Qt::WA_InputMethodEnabled);
1027}

1056void QComboBoxPrivate::_q_dataChanged(const QModelIndex &topLeft, const QModelIndex &bottomRight)
1057{
1058 Q_Q(QComboBox);
1059 if (inserting || topLeft.parent() != root)
1060 return;
1061
1062 if (sizeAdjustPolicy == QComboBox::AdjustToContents) {
1063 sizeHint = QSize();
1064 adjustComboBoxSize();
1065 q->updateGeometry();
1066 }
1067
1068 if (currentIndex.row() >= topLeft.row() && currentIndex.row() <= bottomRight.row()) {
1069 const QString text = q->itemText(index: currentIndex.row());
1070 if (lineEdit) {
1071 lineEdit->setText(text);
1072 updateLineEditGeometry();
1073 } else {
1074 emit q->currentTextChanged(text);
1075 }
1076 q->update();
1077#if QT_CONFIG(accessibility)
1078 QAccessibleValueChangeEvent event(q, text);
1079 QAccessible::updateAccessibility(event: &event);
1080#endif
1081 }

1084void QComboBoxPrivate::_q_rowsInserted(const QModelIndex &parent, int start, int end)
1085{
1086 Q_Q(QComboBox);
1087 if (inserting || parent != root)
1088 return;
1089
1090 if (sizeAdjustPolicy == QComboBox::AdjustToContents) {
1091 sizeHint = QSize();
1092 adjustComboBoxSize();
1093 q->updateGeometry();
1094 }
1095
1096 // set current index if combo was previously empty and there is no placeholderText
1097 if (start == 0 && (end - start + 1) == q->count() && !currentIndex.isValid() &&
1098 placeholderText.isEmpty()) {
1099 q->setCurrentIndex(0);
1100 // need to emit changed if model updated index "silently"
1101 } else if (currentIndex.row() != indexBeforeChange) {
1102 q->update();
1103 _q_emitCurrentIndexChanged(index: currentIndex);
1104 }

1112void QComboBoxPrivate::_q_rowsRemoved(const QModelIndex &parent, int /*start*/, int /*end*/)
1113{
1114 Q_Q(QComboBox);
1115 if (parent != root)
1116 return;
1117
1118 if (sizeAdjustPolicy == QComboBox::AdjustToContents) {
1119 sizeHint = QSize();
1120 adjustComboBoxSize();
1121 q->updateGeometry();
1122 }
1123
1124 // model has changed the currentIndex
1125 if (currentIndex.row() != indexBeforeChange) {
1126 if (!currentIndex.isValid() && q->count()) {
1127 q->setCurrentIndex(qMin(a: q->count() - 1, b: qMax(a: indexBeforeChange, b: 0)));
1128 return;

1132 updateLineEditGeometry();

1177 Initialize \a option with the values from this QComboBox. This method
1178 is useful for subclasses when they need a QStyleOptionComboBox, but don't want

1232Qt::MatchFlags QComboBoxPrivate::matchFlags() const
1233{
1234 // Base how duplicates are determined on the autocompletion case sensitivity
1235 Qt::MatchFlags flags = Qt::MatchFixedString;
1236#if QT_CONFIG(completer)

1244void QComboBoxPrivate::_q_editingFinished()
1245{
1246 Q_Q(QComboBox);
1247 if (!lineEdit)
1248 return;
1249 const auto leText = lineEdit->text();
1250 if (!leText.isEmpty() && itemText(index: currentIndex) != leText) {
1251#if QT_CONFIG(completer)
1252 const auto *leCompleter = lineEdit->completer();
1253 const auto *popup = leCompleter ? QCompleterPrivate::get(o: leCompleter)->popup : nullptr;
1254 if (popup && popup->isVisible()) {
1255 // QLineEdit::editingFinished() will be emitted before the code flow returns
1256 // to QCompleter::eventFilter(), where QCompleter::activated() may be emitted.
1257 // We know that the completer popup will still be visible at this point, and
1258 // that any selection should be valid.
1259 const QItemSelectionModel *selModel = popup->selectionModel();
1260 const QModelIndex curIndex = popup->currentIndex();
1261 const bool completerIsActive = selModel && selModel->selectedIndexes().contains(t: curIndex);
1262
1263 if (completerIsActive)
1264 return;
1265 }
1266#endif
1267 const int index = q_func()->findText(text: leText, flags: matchFlags());
1268 if (index != -1) {
1269 q->setCurrentIndex(index);
1270 emitActivated(index: currentIndex);
1271 }
1272 }

1275
1276void QComboBoxPrivate::_q_returnPressed()
1277{
1278 Q_Q(QComboBox);
1279
1280 // The insertion code below does not apply when the policy is QComboBox::NoInsert.
1281 // In case a completer is installed, item activation via the completer is handled
1282 // in _q_completerActivated(). Otherwise _q_editingFinished() updates the current
1283 // index as appropriate.
1284 if (insertPolicy == QComboBox::NoInsert)
1285 return;
1286
1287 if (lineEdit && !lineEdit->text().isEmpty()) {
1288 if (q->count() >= maxCount && !(this->insertPolicy == QComboBox::InsertAtCurrent))
1289 return;
1290 lineEdit->deselect();
1291 lineEdit->end(mark: false);
1292 QString text = lineEdit->text();
1293 // check for duplicates (if not enabled) and quit
1294 int index = -1;
1295 if (!duplicatesEnabled) {
1296 index = q->findText(text, flags: matchFlags());
1297 if (index != -1) {
1298 q->setCurrentIndex(index);
1299 emitActivated(index: currentIndex);
1300 return;
1301 }
1302 }
1303 switch (insertPolicy) {
1304 case QComboBox::InsertAtTop:
1305 index = 0;
1306 break;
1307 case QComboBox::InsertAtBottom:
1308 index = q->count();
1309 break;
1310 case QComboBox::InsertAtCurrent:
1311 case QComboBox::InsertAfterCurrent:
1312 case QComboBox::InsertBeforeCurrent:
1313 if (!q->count() || !currentIndex.isValid())
1314 index = 0;
1315 else if (insertPolicy == QComboBox::InsertAtCurrent)
1316 q->setItemText(index: q->currentIndex(), text);
1317 else if (insertPolicy == QComboBox::InsertAfterCurrent)
1318 index = q->currentIndex() + 1;
1319 else if (insertPolicy == QComboBox::InsertBeforeCurrent)
1320 index = q->currentIndex();
1321 break;
1322 case QComboBox::InsertAlphabetically:
1323 index = 0;
1324 for (int i = 0; i < q->count(); ++i, ++index) {
1325 if (text.toLower() < q->itemText(index: i).toLower())
1326 break;
1327 }
1328 break;
1329 default:
1330 break;
1331 }
1332 if (index >= 0) {
1333 q->insertItem(aindex: index, atext: text);
1334 q->setCurrentIndex(index);
1335 emitActivated(index: currentIndex);
1336 }
1337 }
1338}

1700/*! \internal
1701 update the default delegate
1702 depending on the style's SH_ComboBox_Popup hint, we use a different default delegate.
1703
1704 but we do not change the delegate is the combobox use a custom delegate,
1705 unless \a force is set to true.
1706 */
1707void QComboBoxPrivate::updateDelegate(bool force)
1708{
1709 Q_Q(QComboBox);
1710 QStyleOptionComboBox opt;
1711 q->initStyleOption(option: &opt);
1712 if (q->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: q)) {
1713 if (force || qobject_cast<QComboBoxDelegate *>(object: q->itemDelegate()))
1714 q->setItemDelegate(new QComboMenuDelegate(q->view(), q));
1715 } else {
1716 if (force || qobject_cast<QComboMenuDelegate *>(object: q->itemDelegate()))
1717 q->setItemDelegate(new QComboBoxDelegate(q->view(), q));
1718 }
1719}

1721QIcon QComboBoxPrivate::itemIcon(const QModelIndex &index) const
1722{
1723 QVariant decoration = model->data(index, role: Qt::DecorationRole);
1724 if (decoration.userType() == QMetaType::QPixmap)
1725 return QIcon(qvariant_cast<QPixmap>(v: decoration));
1726 else
1727 return qvariant_cast<QIcon>(v: decoration);
1728}
1729
1730void QComboBox::setEditable(bool editable)
1731{
1732 Q_D(QComboBox);
1733 if (isEditable() == editable)
1734 return;
1735
1736 QStyleOptionComboBox opt;
1737 initStyleOption(option: &opt);
1738 if (editable) {
1739 if (style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: this)) {
1740 d->viewContainer()->updateScrollers();
1741 view()->setVerticalScrollBarPolicy(Qt::ScrollBarAsNeeded);
1742 }
1743 QLineEdit *le = new QLineEdit(this);
1744 le->setPalette(palette());
1745 setLineEdit(le);
1746 } else {
1747 if (style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: this)) {
1748 d->viewContainer()->updateScrollers();
1749 view()->setVerticalScrollBarPolicy(Qt::ScrollBarAlwaysOff);
1750 }
1751 setAttribute(Qt::WA_InputMethodEnabled, on: false);
1752 d->lineEdit->hide();
1753 d->lineEdit->deleteLater();
1754 d->lineEdit = nullptr;
1755 }
1756
1757 d->updateDelegate();
1758 d->updateFocusPolicy();
1759
1760 d->viewContainer()->updateTopBottomMargin();
1761 if (!testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_Resized))
1762 adjustSize();
1763}

1765/*!
1766 Sets the line \a edit to use instead of the current line edit widget.
1767
1768 The combo box takes ownership of the line edit.
1769
1770 \note Since the combobox's line edit owns the QCompleter, any previous
1771 call to setCompleter() will no longer have any effect.
1772*/
1773void QComboBox::setLineEdit(QLineEdit *edit)
1774{
1775 Q_D(QComboBox);
1776 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!edit)) {
1777 qWarning(msg: "QComboBox::setLineEdit: cannot set a 0 line edit");
1778 return;
1779 }
1780
1781 if (edit == d->lineEdit)
1782 return;
1783
1784 edit->setText(currentText());
1785 delete d->lineEdit;
1786
1787 d->lineEdit = edit;
1788#ifndef QT_NO_IM
1789 qt_widget_private(widget: d->lineEdit)->inheritsInputMethodHints = 1;
1790#endif
1791 if (d->lineEdit->parent() != this)
1792 d->lineEdit->setParent(this);
1793 connect(sender: d->lineEdit, SIGNAL(returnPressed()), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_returnPressed()));
1794 connect(sender: d->lineEdit, SIGNAL(editingFinished()), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_editingFinished()));
1795 connect(sender: d->lineEdit, SIGNAL(textChanged(QString)), receiver: this, SIGNAL(editTextChanged(QString)));
1796 connect(sender: d->lineEdit, SIGNAL(textChanged(QString)), receiver: this, SIGNAL(currentTextChanged(QString)));
1797 connect(sender: d->lineEdit, SIGNAL(cursorPositionChanged(int,int)), receiver: this, SLOT(updateMicroFocus()));
1798 connect(sender: d->lineEdit, SIGNAL(selectionChanged()), receiver: this, SLOT(updateMicroFocus()));
1799 connect(sender: d->lineEdit->d_func()->control, SIGNAL(updateMicroFocus()), receiver: this, SLOT(updateMicroFocus()));
1800 d->lineEdit->setFrame(false);
1801 d->lineEdit->setContextMenuPolicy(Qt::NoContextMenu);
1802 d->updateFocusPolicy();
1803 d->lineEdit->setFocusProxy(this);
1804 d->lineEdit->setAttribute(Qt::WA_MacShowFocusRect, on: false);
1805
1806#if QT_CONFIG(completer)
1807 // create a default completer
1808 if (!d->lineEdit->completer()) {
1809 QCompleter *completer = new QCompleter(d->model, d->lineEdit);
1810 completer->setCaseSensitivity(Qt::CaseInsensitive);
1811 completer->setCompletionMode(QCompleter::InlineCompletion);
1812 completer->setCompletionColumn(d->modelColumn);
1813
1814#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
1815 // Editable combo boxes will have a completer that is set to UnfilteredPopupCompletion.
1816 // This means that when the user enters edit mode they are immediately presented with a
1817 // list of possible completions.
1818 if (QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled())
1819 completer->setCompletionMode(QCompleter::UnfilteredPopupCompletion);
1820#endif
1821 // sets up connections
1822 setCompleter(completer);
1823 }
1824#endif
1825
1826 setAttribute(Qt::WA_InputMethodEnabled);
1827 d->updateLayoutDirection();
1828 d->updateLineEditGeometry();
1829 if (isVisible())
1830 d->lineEdit->show();
1831
1832 update();
1833}

1965 that->setModel(new QStandardItemModel(0, 1, that));

1970/*!
1971 Sets the model to be \a model. \a model must not be \nullptr.
1972 If you want to clear the contents of a model, call clear().
1973
1974 \note If the combobox is editable, then the \a model will also be
1975 set on the completer of the line edit.
1976
1977 \sa clear() setCompleter()
1978*/
1979void QComboBox::setModel(QAbstractItemModel *model)
1980{
1981 Q_D(QComboBox);
1982
1983 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!model)) {
1984 qWarning(msg: "QComboBox::setModel: cannot set a 0 model");
1985 return;
1986 }
1987
1988 if (model == d->model)
1989 return;
1990
1991#if QT_CONFIG(completer)
1992 if (d->lineEdit && d->lineEdit->completer())
1993 d->lineEdit->completer()->setModel(model);
1994#endif
1995 if (d->model) {
1996 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(dataChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)),
1997 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_dataChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)));
1998 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsAboutToBeInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
1999 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_updateIndexBeforeChange()));
2000 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
2001 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)));
2002 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsAboutToBeRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
2003 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_updateIndexBeforeChange()));
2004 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
2005 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
2006 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(destroyed()),
2007 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_modelDestroyed()));
2008 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(modelAboutToBeReset()),
2009 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_updateIndexBeforeChange()));
2010 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(modelReset()),
2011 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_modelReset()));
2012 if (d->model->QObject::parent() == this)
2013 delete d->model;
2014 }
2015
2016 d->model = model;
2017
2018 connect(sender: model, SIGNAL(dataChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)),
2019 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_dataChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)));
2020 connect(sender: model, SIGNAL(rowsAboutToBeInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
2021 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_updateIndexBeforeChange()));
2022 connect(sender: model, SIGNAL(rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
2023 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)));
2024 connect(sender: model, SIGNAL(rowsAboutToBeRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
2025 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_updateIndexBeforeChange()));
2026 connect(sender: model, SIGNAL(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
2027 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
2028 connect(sender: model, SIGNAL(destroyed()),
2029 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_modelDestroyed()));
2030 connect(sender: model, SIGNAL(modelAboutToBeReset()),
2031 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_updateIndexBeforeChange()));
2032 connect(sender: model, SIGNAL(modelReset()),
2033 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_modelReset()));
2034
2035 if (d->container) {
2036 d->container->itemView()->setModel(model);
2037 connect(sender: d->container->itemView()->selectionModel(),
2038 SIGNAL(currentChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)),
2039 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_emitHighlighted(QModelIndex)), Qt::UniqueConnection);
2040 }

2476 QPlatformTheme *theme = QGuiApplicationPrivate::instance()->platformTheme();

2478 if (!m_platformMenu)

2483

2532/*!
2533 Displays the list of items in the combobox. If the list is empty
2534 then no items will be shown.
2535
2536 If you reimplement this function to show a custom pop-up, make
2537 sure you call hidePopup() to reset the internal state.
2538

2540*/

2542{
2543 Q_D(QComboBox);
2544 if (count() <= 0)

2546

2631

2637 }

2639 //we need to activate the layout to make sure the min/maximum size are set when the widget was not yet show
2640 container->layout()->activate();

2642 listRect.setSize( listRect.size().expandedTo(otherSize: container->minimumSize())
2643 .boundedTo(otherSize: container->maximumSize()));
2644

2646 if (boundToScreen) {

2651 above.setX(screen.x() + screen.width() - listRect.width());

2654 below.setX(screen.x());
2655 above.setX(screen.x());
2656 }
2657 }
2658

2667 listRect.moveTop(pos: above.y() + offset - listRect.top());
2668

2670 // available screen geometry.This may override the vertical position, but it is more
2671 // important to show as much as possible of the popup.
2672 const int height = !boundToScreen ? listRect.height() : qMin(a: listRect.height(), b: screen.height());

2674
2675 if (boundToScreen) {
2676 if (listRect.top() < screen.top())
2677 listRect.moveTop(pos: screen.top());
2678 if (listRect.bottom() > screen.bottom())
2679 listRect.moveBottom(pos: screen.bottom());
2680 }
2681 } else if (!boundToScreen || listRect.height() <= belowHeight) {
2682 listRect.moveTopLeft(p: below);
2683 } else if (listRect.height() <= aboveHeight) {
2684 listRect.moveBottomLeft(p: above);
2685 } else if (belowHeight >= aboveHeight) {
2686 listRect.setHeight(belowHeight);
2687 listRect.moveTopLeft(p: below);
2688 } else {
2689 listRect.setHeight(aboveHeight);
2690 listRect.moveBottomLeft(p: above);
2691 }
2692
2693 if (qApp) {
2694 QGuiApplication::inputMethod()->reset();
2695 }
2696
2697 const QScrollBar *sb = view()->horizontalScrollBar();
2698 const auto needHorizontalScrollBar = [this, sb]{
2699 const Qt::ScrollBarPolicy policy = view()->horizontalScrollBarPolicy();
2700 return (policy == Qt::ScrollBarAsNeeded || policy == Qt::ScrollBarAlwaysOn)
2701 && sb->minimum() < sb->maximum();
2702 };
2703 const bool neededHorizontalScrollBar = needHorizontalScrollBar();
2704 if (neededHorizontalScrollBar)
2705 listRect.adjust(dx1: 0, dy1: 0, dx2: 0, dy2: sb->height());
2706
2707 // Hide the scrollers here, so that the listrect gets the full height of the container
2708 // If the scrollers are truly needed, the later call to container->updateScrollers()
2709 // will make them visible again.
2710 container->hideScrollers();
2711 container->setGeometry(listRect);
2712
2713#ifndef Q_OS_MAC
2714 const bool updatesEnabled = container->updatesEnabled();
2715#endif
2716
2717#if QT_CONFIG(effects)
2718 bool scrollDown = (listRect.topLeft() == below);
2719 if (QApplication::isEffectEnabled(Qt::UI_AnimateCombo)
2720 && !style->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: this) && !window()->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_DontShowOnScreen))
2721 qScrollEffect(container, dir: scrollDown ? QEffects::DownScroll : QEffects::UpScroll, time: 150);
2722#endif
2723
2724// Don't disable updates on OS X. Windows are displayed immediately on this platform,
2725// which means that the window will be visible before the call to container->show() returns.
2726// If updates are disabled at this point we'll miss our chance at painting the popup
2727// menu before it's shown, causing flicker since the window then displays the standard gray
2728// background.
2729#ifndef Q_OS_MAC
2730 container->setUpdatesEnabled(false);
2731#endif
2732
2733 bool startTimer = !container->isVisible();
2734 container->raise();
2735 container->create();
2736 if (QWindow *containerWindow = qt_widget_private(widget: container)->windowHandle(mode: QWidgetPrivate::WindowHandleMode::TopLevel)) {
2737 QScreen *currentScreen = d->associatedScreen();
2738 if (currentScreen && !currentScreen->virtualSiblings().contains(t: containerWindow->screen())) {
2739 containerWindow->setScreen(currentScreen);
2740
2741 // This seems to workaround an issue in xcb+multi GPU+multiscreen
2742 // environment where the window might not always show up when screen
2743 // is changed.
2744 container->hide();
2745 }
2746 }
2747 container->show();
2748 if (!neededHorizontalScrollBar && needHorizontalScrollBar()) {
2749 listRect.adjust(dx1: 0, dy1: 0, dx2: 0, dy2: sb->height());
2750 container->setGeometry(listRect);
2751 }
2752
2753 container->updateScrollers();
2754 view()->setFocus();
2755
2756 view()->scrollTo(index: view()->currentIndex(),
2757 hint: style->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ComboBox_Popup, opt: &opt, widget: this)
2758 ? QAbstractItemView::PositionAtCenter
2759 : QAbstractItemView::EnsureVisible);
2760
2761#ifndef Q_OS_MAC
2762 container->setUpdatesEnabled(updatesEnabled);
2763#endif
2764
2765 container->update();
2766 if (startTimer) {
2767 container->popupTimer.start();
2768 container->maybeIgnoreMouseButtonRelease = true;
2769 }
2770}

2772/*!
2773 Hides the list of items in the combobox if it is currently visible
2774 and resets the internal state, so that if the custom pop-up was
2775 shown inside the reimplemented showPopup(), then you also need to
2776 reimplement the hidePopup() function to hide your custom pop-up
2777 and call the base class implementation to reset the internal state
2778 whenever your custom pop-up widget is hidden.

2783{
2784 Q_D(QComboBox);
2785 if (d->hidingPopup)
2786 return;
2787 d->hidingPopup = true;
2788 // can't use QBoolBlocker on a bitfield
2789 auto resetHidingPopup = qScopeGuard(f: [d]{
2790 d->hidingPopup = false;
2791 });
2792
2793 if (!d->container || !d->container->isVisible())

2796#if QT_CONFIG(effects)

2800 ? d->container->itemView()->selectionModel() : nullptr;

3117/*!
3118 \reimp
3119*/
3120void QComboBox::keyPressEvent(QKeyEvent *e)
3121{
3122 Q_D(QComboBox);
3123
3124#if QT_CONFIG(completer)
3125 if (const auto *cmpltr = completer()) {
3126 const auto *popup = QCompleterPrivate::get(o: cmpltr)->popup;
3127 if (popup && popup->isVisible()) {
3128 // provide same autocompletion support as line edit
3129 d->lineEdit->event(e);
3130 return;
3131 }
3132 }
3133#endif
3134
3135 enum Move { NoMove=0 , MoveUp , MoveDown , MoveFirst , MoveLast};
3136
3137 Move move = NoMove;
3138 int newIndex = currentIndex();
3139
3140 bool pressLikeButton = !d->lineEdit;
3141#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
3142 pressLikeButton |= QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled() && !hasEditFocus();
3143#endif
3144 auto key = e->key();
3145 if (pressLikeButton) {
3146 const auto buttonPressKeys = QGuiApplicationPrivate::platformTheme()
3147 ->themeHint(hint: QPlatformTheme::ButtonPressKeys)
3148 .value<QList<Qt::Key>>();
3149 if (buttonPressKeys.contains(t: key)) {
3150 showPopup();
3151 return;
3152 }
3153 }
3154
3155 switch (key) {
3156 case Qt::Key_Up:
3157 if (e->modifiers() & Qt::ControlModifier)
3158 break; // pass to line edit for auto completion
3159 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
3160 case Qt::Key_PageUp:
3161#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
3162 if (QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled())
3163 e->ignore();
3164 else
3165#endif
3166 move = MoveUp;
3167 break;
3168 case Qt::Key_Down:
3169 if (e->modifiers() & Qt::AltModifier) {
3170 showPopup();
3171 return;
3172 } else if (e->modifiers() & Qt::ControlModifier)
3173 break; // pass to line edit for auto completion
3174 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
3175 case Qt::Key_PageDown:
3176#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
3177 if (QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled())
3178 e->ignore();
3179 else
3180#endif
3181 move = MoveDown;
3182 break;
3183 case Qt::Key_Home:
3184 if (!d->lineEdit)
3185 move = MoveFirst;
3186 break;
3187 case Qt::Key_End:
3188 if (!d->lineEdit)
3189 move = MoveLast;
3190 break;
3191 case Qt::Key_F4:
3192 if (!e->modifiers()) {
3193 showPopup();
3194 return;
3195 }
3196 break;
3197 case Qt::Key_Enter:
3198 case Qt::Key_Return:
3199 case Qt::Key_Escape:
3200 if (!d->lineEdit)
3201 e->ignore();
3202 break;
3203#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
3204 case Qt::Key_Left:
3205 case Qt::Key_Right:
3206 if (QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled() && !hasEditFocus())
3207 e->ignore();
3208 break;
3209 case Qt::Key_Back:
3210 if (QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled()) {
3211 if (!hasEditFocus() || !d->lineEdit)
3212 e->ignore();
3213 } else {
3214 e->ignore(); // let the surrounding dialog have it
3215 }
3216 break;
3217#endif
3218 default:
3219#if QT_CONFIG(shortcut)
3220 if (d->container && d->container->isVisible() && e->matches(key: QKeySequence::Cancel)) {
3221 hidePopup();
3222 e->accept();
3223 }
3224#endif
3225
3226 if (!d->lineEdit) {
3227 if (!e->text().isEmpty())
3228 d->keyboardSearchString(text: e->text());
3229 else
3230 e->ignore();
3231 }
3232 }
3233
3234 const int rowCount = count();
3235
3236 if (move != NoMove) {
3237 e->accept();
3238 switch (move) {
3239 case MoveFirst:
3240 newIndex = -1;
3241 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
3242 case MoveDown:
3243 newIndex++;
3244 while (newIndex < rowCount && !(d->model->index(row: newIndex, column: d->modelColumn, parent: d->root).flags() & Qt::ItemIsEnabled))
3245 newIndex++;
3246 break;
3247 case MoveLast:
3248 newIndex = rowCount;
3249 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
3250 case MoveUp:
3251 newIndex--;
3252 while ((newIndex >= 0) && !(d->model->flags(index: d->model->index(row: newIndex,column: d->modelColumn,parent: d->root)) & Qt::ItemIsEnabled))
3253 newIndex--;
3254 break;
3255 default:
3256 e->ignore();
3257 break;
3258 }
3259
3260 if (newIndex >= 0 && newIndex < rowCount && newIndex != currentIndex()) {
3261 setCurrentIndex(newIndex);
3262 d->emitActivated(index: d->currentIndex);
3263 }
3264 } else if (d->lineEdit) {
3265 d->lineEdit->event(e);
3266 }
3267}
